{

	iif Functions v1.0
		Curt Laubscher (DorkeyDear)

	Description
		The implicit conversions of types to and from variants increases execution time. These functions are to avoid those conversions, thus increasing execution time.

	Version 1.0 on 26 May 2010 12:14 EST by Curt
		Created iif functions for many types

}

function iif_bool(const Test, IfTrue, IfFalse: boolean): boolean;
begin
	if (Test) then
		Result := IfTrue
	else
		Result := IfFalse;
end;

